cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of 3D object pose estimation using RGB images and CAD models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method that involves learning local RGB to CAD correspondences, which falls under the scope of robotics and automation (cs.RO). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to learn how to select keypoints and enforce viewpoint and modality invariance, which falls under the scope of machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with 3D object modeling and rendering, which falls under the scope of graphics (cs.GR).
